create repo:$ git init

link to the repo in Github:git remote add origin "https://github.com/atanughosh85/git-github.git"

pull files from the master repo in Github:git pull origin master

check the files are added to index and ready to commit:git status

Add file(gitCommands.txt) to the index: git add gitCommands
Add multiple files to index together: git add -A

add/update index: git commit -m "Adding the gitCommands file to GitHub"
add/update index:git commit -a -m "Adding all files together"

check logs:git log

create a new branch: git branch firstbranch

switch to new branch: git checkout firstbranch

add new files to the new branch: git add TestFile3.txt

commit the new file to the new branch: git commit -m "Adding the TestFile3 to the new branch"

list all files:ls

move back to master branch:git checkout master

Merge the new branch into master branch(You should be inside master branch):git merge firstbranch

Note i can make more changes to firstbranch, it will not affect the master, until we merge with master






































push to master Github repo from local repo: